1
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:21,067
I'm so confused.

2
00:00:21,133 --> 00:00:24,133
Why is it like this?
Why am I thinking of Mikoy?

3
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:25,900
He's in my mind.

4
00:00:25,967 --> 00:00:27,800
Didn't you and Celeste
patch things up?

5
00:00:27,867 --> 00:00:30,633
What will I look forward to
from your love story?

6
00:00:30,700 --> 00:00:33,500
Grandmother, she's now
with the man she will marry.

7
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:35,233
You have nothing
to look forward to.

8
00:00:35,300 --> 00:00:37,267
So, it's really over for you
and Celeste

9
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:38,633
even if lightning strikes you?

10
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:40,467
You might want to join us
for snacks?

11
00:00:40,533 --> 00:00:43,667
It's should be just you
and Celeste.

12
00:00:43,733 --> 00:00:46,367
Anyway, thank you
for your invitation.

13
00:00:46,433 --> 00:00:47,700
Welcome, Sir.

14
00:00:47,767 --> 00:00:50,600
Don't call me Sir.

15
00:00:50,667 --> 00:00:54,333
It would be better
if you just call me father.

16
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:58,400
How can you and Mommy be okay
if Celeste is in your life?

17
00:00:58,467 --> 00:00:59,833
I just don't want to give you
false hopes

18
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:01,600
that your Mommy and I
will get back together.

19
00:01:01,667 --> 00:01:03,067
We have our own lives now.

20
00:01:03,133 --> 00:01:04,633
How about me?

21
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:07,867
I'll always be here for you
and I will always love you.

22
00:01:07,967 --> 00:01:10,900
So please don't feel bad
about Daddy.

23
00:01:10,967 --> 00:01:12,933
But I still don't like Celeste.

24
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,733
And I feel like I never will.

25
00:01:14,800 --> 00:01:16,800
I'm just so happy that somehow,

26
00:01:16,867 --> 00:01:18,733
you and your father
are getting okay.

27
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:21,300
But maybe if Mother
is still here

28
00:01:21,367 --> 00:01:24,167
it will be easier for me
to forgive them.

29
00:01:24,233 --> 00:01:25,500
You are a good person, Celeste.

30
00:01:25,567 --> 00:01:27,600
And I'm confident
that sooner or later

31
00:01:27,667 --> 00:01:29,800
you will be able
to finally forgive them.

32
00:01:29,867 --> 00:01:32,033
You'll be able
to finally forgive yourself.

33
00:01:51,133 --> 00:01:52,467
Let's go there!

34
00:01:52,533 --> 00:01:54,767
You might fall.

35
00:01:54,833 --> 00:01:57,500
Hurry, let's go there.

36
00:01:57,567 --> 00:01:58,633
Come on.

37
00:01:58,700 --> 00:02:00,367
Here we are.

38
00:02:00,433 --> 00:02:01,667
What?

39
00:02:01,733 --> 00:02:03,700
- It's good, right?
- Wow!

40
00:02:03,767 --> 00:02:05,967
It's beautiful here.
You know what? You're right.

41
00:02:06,033 --> 00:02:06,867
It's really beautiful.

42
00:02:08,233 --> 00:02:09,667
I'm happy that you like it.

43
00:02:11,700 --> 00:02:13,167
You know someday

44
00:02:14,233 --> 00:02:16,267
this is where I'll ask you
to marry me.

45
00:02:16,333 --> 00:02:18,333
Hey, what's with you?

46
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:20,367
What are you thinking?

47
00:02:20,433 --> 00:02:23,133
You know,
please let's study first.

48
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,767
Okay, I'll report you
to Grandmother Ikay.

49
00:02:24,833 --> 00:02:25,967
Would you like that?

50
00:02:26,033 --> 00:02:27,433
Go ahead and tell her.
It's up to you.

51
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:28,733
But me, I'm sure

52
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:30,267
that you're the one
I want to be with

53
00:02:30,333 --> 00:02:31,100
for the rest of my life.

54
00:02:33,733 --> 00:02:35,367
Where are you going?

55
00:02:35,433 --> 00:02:36,400
It's nothing.

56
00:02:36,467 --> 00:02:37,867
- What will do there?
- It's nothing.

57
00:02:37,933 --> 00:02:40,100
- Just a second.
- Mikoy, it's not allowed there.

58
00:02:40,167 --> 00:02:41,800
- Come back here.
- Leave it to me.

59
00:02:41,867 --> 00:02:43,433
You will be scolded.

60
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:47,333
Give me your hand.

61
00:02:49,933 --> 00:02:51,800
- What is that for?
- Celeste...

62
00:02:51,867 --> 00:02:54,067
I know that we're still young.

63
00:02:54,133 --> 00:02:57,900
But I believe
in what Grandmother Ikay said

64
00:02:59,067 --> 00:03:02,100
that there is someone destined
for everyone.

65
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:06,400
If two people are destined
for each other,

66
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,633
even if they are separated
for years,

67
00:03:10,867 --> 00:03:14,333
no matter what happens,
they will go back to each other.

68
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:16,067
Do you know what it is called?

69
00:03:17,067 --> 00:03:17,367
What?

70
00:03:18,533 --> 00:03:19,167
True love.

71
00:03:21,433 --> 00:03:21,967
Celeste...

72
00:03:23,167 --> 00:03:24,233
What are you doing?

73
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:26,400
Let the Bulusan Lake
be a witness,

74
00:03:26,467 --> 00:03:29,067
all the trees here,
all the flowers.

75
00:03:29,133 --> 00:03:30,533
Answer my question, Celeste.

76
00:03:32,367 --> 00:03:34,333
Can you be my happily ever
after?

77
00:03:37,667 --> 00:03:39,067
Come on.

78
00:03:39,133 --> 00:03:40,500
Let's be the future
of each other,

79
00:03:41,900 --> 00:03:42,867
please?

80
00:03:42,933 --> 00:03:45,100
You know a lot, Mikoy.

81
00:03:45,167 --> 00:03:47,100
Come on, please.

82
00:03:47,167 --> 00:03:48,867
It's up to you.
I won't stand up here.

83
00:03:48,933 --> 00:03:50,967
Even if I kneel here
for a hundred years.

84
00:03:51,033 --> 00:03:54,700
Even if I grow old,
even if lost all my teeth.

85
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:56,600
I will not stand up
until you say yes.

86
00:03:56,667 --> 00:03:57,133
Please?

87
00:03:59,400 --> 00:03:59,967
Please.

88
00:04:01,967 --> 00:04:02,867
Okay.

89
00:04:03,900 --> 00:04:05,733
What do you mean okay?
Are you sure?

90
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:06,833
What do you mean okay?

91
00:04:06,900 --> 00:04:08,100
- Yes?
- Yes.

92
00:04:08,167 --> 00:04:09,133
Yes?

93
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:10,733
- Yes.
- Yes? Are you sure?

94
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:12,600
- Yes.
- Yes!

95
00:04:12,667 --> 00:04:13,600
Yes!
Celeste!

96
00:04:44,300 --> 00:04:44,667
Love,

97
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,733
this place is so romantic.

98
00:04:50,267 --> 00:04:54,167
If only I saw this place
before maybe I proposed here.

99
00:05:02,567 --> 00:05:03,233
It's Vivian.

100
00:05:04,900 --> 00:05:06,600
Why don't you answer it?
Maybe it's important.

101
00:05:09,133 --> 00:05:10,433
Is there anything more important
than you?

102
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:19,000
Love, you are the most important
thing in my life right now.

103
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,433
And I love you so much.

104
00:06:38,633 --> 00:06:39,133
Are you okay?

105
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:41,067
Do I look like I'm okay?

106
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:44,667
You're grouchy.

107
00:06:44,733 --> 00:06:45,600
I'm just asking.

108
00:06:47,167 --> 00:06:50,433
Do you know that a grouchy
person will become ugly?

109
00:06:51,633 --> 00:06:52,867
It's like this.

110
00:06:52,933 --> 00:06:53,500
Look at me.

111
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,067
Is that ugly?

112
00:07:00,967 --> 00:07:02,100
Make it uglier.

113
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:12,233
- Oh my God.
- You know it suits you,

114
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:14,000
just be happy.

115
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:18,100
You know, life is short
to be sad or grouchy.

116
00:07:19,767 --> 00:07:20,833
You know, you have a point.

117
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:25,967
Hey, how long you guys
have been here?

118
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:33,000
Hey, what's so funny?

119
00:07:34,967 --> 00:07:35,933
A grouchy person...

120
00:07:36,967 --> 00:07:38,000
will become ugly.

121
00:07:39,433 --> 00:07:40,567
You're weird.

122
00:07:41,633 --> 00:07:43,667
- We have things to get.
- Wait.

123
00:07:43,733 --> 00:07:44,833
Come on, let's go.

124
00:07:45,900 --> 00:07:46,700
You're too much.

125
00:07:47,767 --> 00:07:50,300
- I'm still laughing.
- Come on, let's go.

126
00:07:50,367 --> 00:07:51,300
He's grouchy.

127
00:07:53,300 --> 00:07:54,000
Sorry.

128
00:08:08,567 --> 00:08:10,033
I think I still can catch up
in the meeting

129
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:11,633
that I moved to this morning.

130
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:13,467
- That's good.
- I just really want

131
00:08:13,533 --> 00:08:16,867
to visit you
and check if you're okay

132
00:08:16,933 --> 00:08:18,467
and also, to visit Tiffany.

133
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,967
Sorry for leaving you so soon,
Love.

134
00:08:23,033 --> 00:08:25,733
No, it's okay. Don't worry,
I understand.

135
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:28,000
Next time we should go out again
with Tiffany.

136
00:08:28,067 --> 00:08:29,867
Yes, that would be lovely.

137
00:08:29,933 --> 00:08:32,333
So the three of us
can have a bonding moment.

138
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:35,200
I know she still has
a resistance

139
00:08:35,267 --> 00:08:36,400
to our wedding plans.

140
00:08:37,367 --> 00:08:39,700
It's okay. You know,
I understand.

141
00:08:39,767 --> 00:08:42,433
And I'm willing to wait
when she's ready.

142
00:08:43,767 --> 00:08:45,267
I'm really so lucky to have you.

143
00:08:46,433 --> 00:08:48,600
I wasn't wrong
that it's you I loved.

144
00:08:51,667 --> 00:08:52,167
Take care.

145
00:09:26,567 --> 00:09:30,400
Let me guess who you will meet.

146
00:09:30,500 --> 00:09:32,533
It's Celeste.

147
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:33,767
No, Grandmother.

148
00:09:33,833 --> 00:09:35,767
I will meet the Mayor.

149
00:09:35,833 --> 00:09:36,900
What?

150
00:09:36,967 --> 00:09:39,133
You almost bathed in perfume.

151
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:41,900
You will meet Mayor?

152
00:09:41,967 --> 00:09:44,267
Why? Will Mayor smell you?

153
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:46,600
Grandmother, you already knew
who I will meet.

154
00:09:46,667 --> 00:09:48,600
You know that it's Celeste
and you're still asking.

155
00:09:49,733 --> 00:09:51,433
You're just going there
and I'm already on my way back.

156
00:09:52,467 --> 00:09:53,467
Why didn't we meet?

157
00:09:54,533 --> 00:09:55,867
You're such a smart aleck.

158
00:09:55,933 --> 00:09:58,367
The problem with you
is you don't want to admit it.

159
00:09:58,433 --> 00:10:00,000
You want to be exposed.

160
00:10:02,767 --> 00:10:04,233
I'll go ahead, Grandmother.

161
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:06,067
Okay, you take care.

162
00:10:07,467 --> 00:10:09,100
Update me later.

163
00:10:09,167 --> 00:10:10,533
Tell me a lot.

164
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:12,033
Something that I want to hear.

165
00:10:12,100 --> 00:10:13,733
Okay, Mikoy?

166
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:15,567
I'll tell you ten sacks
of stories.

167
00:10:15,633 --> 00:10:16,767
That's good. Bye.

168
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:18,200
Bye, Grandmother.

169
00:10:18,267 --> 00:10:20,167
Update me later. I'll wait.

170
00:10:29,867 --> 00:10:31,700
Father is good, right?

171
00:10:31,767 --> 00:10:34,700
He covered your phone with rice
that's why the moisture is gone.

172
00:10:36,667 --> 00:10:37,733
Thank you, Father.

173
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:39,067
Okay, Celeste.

174
00:10:39,133 --> 00:10:41,433
By the way, how was your trip?

175
00:10:41,500 --> 00:10:42,700
It was okay, Father.

176
00:10:42,767 --> 00:10:44,500
- Actually, we'll go back...
- Cuz!

177
00:10:44,567 --> 00:10:45,800
Cuz!

178
00:10:45,867 --> 00:10:46,800
How are you?

179
00:10:46,867 --> 00:10:49,233
I heard that you and Mikoy
got stranded.

180
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:50,700
Are you okay?

181
00:10:50,767 --> 00:10:52,900
How is your flawless skin?

182
00:10:52,967 --> 00:10:54,033
I'm okay.

183
00:10:54,100 --> 00:10:56,067
- Are you okay?
- I'm okay.

184
00:10:56,133 --> 00:10:57,233
Why are you here?

185
00:10:58,533 --> 00:11:00,000
I was worried about you.

186
00:11:00,067 --> 00:11:03,367
I just want to know
how you are and talk to you.

187
00:11:03,433 --> 00:11:05,367
The truth, what happened?

188
00:11:05,433 --> 00:11:06,633
What's the score between you
and Mikoy.

189
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:07,500
Tell me.

190
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:11,333
You know, thank you
for the concern.

191
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:16,000
Let's talk some other time
because Mikoy and I will leave.

192
00:11:16,067 --> 00:11:16,433
He's here.

193
00:11:18,067 --> 00:11:19,067
Hi.

194
00:11:19,133 --> 00:11:20,033
Hi, Mikoy.

195
00:11:20,100 --> 00:11:22,933
Where are we going today?

196
00:11:24,267 --> 00:11:24,800
Paguriran.

197
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:28,267
Paguriran? The lagoon?

198
00:11:28,333 --> 00:11:29,433
Yeah.

199
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:31,500
Is that where
there are big bats?

200
00:11:31,567 --> 00:11:33,200
Celeste is afraid of that.

201
00:11:34,667 --> 00:11:35,200
I cannot.

202
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:37,767
I can't take the big bat.

203
00:11:37,833 --> 00:11:40,633
Celeste, it's beautiful there,
I promise.

204
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:41,167
It's beautiful.

205
00:11:42,333 --> 00:11:42,700
No.

206
00:11:43,700 --> 00:11:46,200
Mikoy, can we go somewhere else,
please?

207
00:11:46,267 --> 00:11:47,067
We have to go there.

208
00:11:47,133 --> 00:11:48,533
Here's the thing.
There's an event.

209
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:51,233
Mayor said to include that
in your community service

210
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:52,267
so it will be promoted.

211
00:11:53,633 --> 00:11:55,000
Oh my God, Mikoy.
I can't do that.

212
00:11:55,067 --> 00:11:59,133
Anywhere in Sorsogon
but not in that lagoon.

213
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,433
Just thinking about the bats,

214
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:02,933
I'm getting goose pimples
already.

215
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:04,267
I'm traumatized.
I can't do that.

216
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:04,600
Please.

217
00:12:06,167 --> 00:12:07,500
Wait, I heard that.

218
00:12:07,567 --> 00:12:09,400
There's an event.
There's dancing.

219
00:12:09,467 --> 00:12:13,000
It's like I want to join
so I can do this.

220
00:12:13,067 --> 00:12:14,033
I'll join you there.

221
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:15,867
Are you also joining, Uncle?

222
00:12:15,967 --> 00:12:17,267
- I can't.
- I'll come with you.

223
00:12:17,333 --> 00:12:20,900
I'll take care of you, okay?

224
00:12:22,900 --> 00:12:24,800
Okay, but we won't be long.

225
00:12:24,867 --> 00:12:27,600
Yes. We won't be long, okay?

226
00:12:27,667 --> 00:12:29,633
Okay. I'll just change
my clothes.

227
00:12:29,700 --> 00:12:31,133
Yeah. It looks like you should.

228
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:32,700
I might get bitten by a bat.

229
00:12:32,767 --> 00:12:34,300
It might bite a big chunk
from me.

230
00:12:38,267 --> 00:12:39,267
Let's join.

231
00:12:39,333 --> 00:12:39,800
That'll be fun.

232
00:12:41,233 --> 00:12:43,167
Mikoy, okay?

233
00:12:43,233 --> 00:12:45,400
We'll do this later.

234
00:12:45,467 --> 00:12:46,067
May-may.

235
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:47,767
Sit.

236
00:12:48,933 --> 00:12:49,367
Okay.

237
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:38,033
Celeste, are you okay?

238
00:13:40,867 --> 00:13:42,200
Can we just cancel?

239
00:13:42,267 --> 00:13:45,600
When we were young, you said
that there's a big bat there.

240
00:13:45,667 --> 00:13:46,133
This is it.

241
00:14:03,067 --> 00:14:05,567
It's really beautiful
here in Paguriran.

242
00:14:05,633 --> 00:14:08,333
It's like it's really fun
whenever you see it.

243
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:09,867
It's just for happy thoughts.

244
00:14:09,933 --> 00:14:12,000
That's why I brought you here,
right?

245
00:14:12,067 --> 00:14:13,533
I want to see you happy.

246
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:15,767
How about you, Mikoy?

247
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:16,900
Are you happy?

248
00:14:16,967 --> 00:14:20,033
Yes, of course.
I'm happy when I'm with you.

249
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:21,400
Me too, Mikoy.

250
00:14:21,467 --> 00:14:25,100
I feel safe when I'm with you.

251
00:14:25,167 --> 00:14:26,800
I will take care of you.

252
00:14:26,867 --> 00:14:29,400
Whatever danger, I'll save you.

253
00:14:29,500 --> 00:14:30,067
Like that.

254
00:14:31,300 --> 00:14:33,333
- Why? What did you see?
- Oh my...

255
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:34,467
- Celeste...
- What?

256
00:14:34,533 --> 00:14:36,267
There's a giant bat.

257
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:38,100
Hey! What? A giant bat?

258
00:14:38,167 --> 00:14:39,933
Mikoy, let's go home.
Come on, come on, Mikoy...

259
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,100
Don't worry.

260
00:14:41,167 --> 00:14:42,100
I'll take care of you, Celeste.

261
00:14:42,167 --> 00:14:44,700
- No, let's go.
- I'll take care of you.

262
00:14:44,767 --> 00:14:47,033
- Let's go, let's go.
- The view is very beautiful.

263
00:14:47,100 --> 00:14:48,700
No.

264
00:14:48,767 --> 00:14:50,867
That bat is nothing.

265
00:14:50,933 --> 00:14:52,933
Mikoy, let's go.

266
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:55,533
Please, let's get out of here.

267
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:56,567
- Come on.
- I'll take care of you,

268
00:14:56,633 --> 00:14:57,633
- Celeste.
- Let's go.

269
00:14:57,700 --> 00:15:00,000
- Trust me, Celeste.
- I don't like bats.

270
00:15:00,067 --> 00:15:02,233
Let's go, Mikoy. Let's go.

271
00:15:02,333 --> 00:15:03,567
My God, Mikoy.

272
00:15:03,633 --> 00:15:06,967
This is it, right? You told me
that there's a big bat here.

273
00:15:08,433 --> 00:15:10,133
It's there. It might come out.

274
00:15:11,633 --> 00:15:13,933
- I might get rabies.
- Relax, relax.

275
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:15,933
What if it bites my finger?

276
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,767
Just relax. I'm here.

277
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:20,567
Mikoy, don't leave me.

278
00:15:20,633 --> 00:15:22,033
I won't leave you, okay?

279
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:22,567
Come here.

280
00:15:23,667 --> 00:15:25,867
I won't leave you, okay?

281
00:15:36,467 --> 00:15:36,933
Bro...

282
00:15:39,167 --> 00:15:39,933
it's not starting.

283
00:15:41,167 --> 00:15:43,267
Good thing we are not yet far
from your house.

284
00:15:43,333 --> 00:15:45,067
Let's go to Berong,
the mechanic.

285
00:15:47,867 --> 00:15:48,433
Okay.

286
00:15:52,133 --> 00:15:54,267
Basti, just stay here.

287
00:15:54,333 --> 00:15:55,867
We'll just fetch the mechanic.

288
00:15:55,933 --> 00:15:57,333
Yes, Mr. Ben.

289
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:57,700
Come on.

290
00:16:03,533 --> 00:16:05,267
Move aside. The show is over.

291
00:16:06,467 --> 00:16:07,833
You're really a villain.

292
00:16:08,933 --> 00:16:10,533
I'm the villain?

293
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:11,833
I'm the boyfriend.

294
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:12,400
Go ahead.

295
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:14,467
Go ahead, James. Say it loud.

296
00:16:14,533 --> 00:16:15,800
Why don't you tell them?

297
00:16:17,900 --> 00:16:20,267
- It's his fault.
- Wait.

298
00:16:20,333 --> 00:16:21,467
Here you again.

299
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:25,233
Can you just cooperate?

300
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:27,967
It won't be long
and this will end?

301
00:16:28,033 --> 00:16:29,433
So please, just one.

302
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:31,133
I beg you, guys.

303
00:16:32,300 --> 00:16:32,867
Please.

304
00:16:34,300 --> 00:16:35,433
It's his fault.

305
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:36,700
Do you think this is all real?

306
00:16:36,767 --> 00:16:37,700
What's with you, James?
Are you crazy?

307
00:16:38,667 --> 00:16:39,500
I'm just acting.

308
00:16:40,667 --> 00:16:41,867
What can I do
if I'm good at acting?

309
00:16:41,967 --> 00:16:42,933
What's with you?

310
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:45,467
I even convinced you
with my acting.

311
00:16:45,533 --> 00:16:46,567
Okay.

312
00:16:46,633 --> 00:16:51,500
You know I will knock your heads
if you won't stop.

313
00:16:56,667 --> 00:16:59,133
No one will talk.

314
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:05,500
James?

315
00:17:22,667 --> 00:17:25,600
You are a big disappointment,
Tonito.

316
00:17:25,667 --> 00:17:28,433
We lost a multi-million
investment project

317
00:17:28,500 --> 00:17:29,867
because of your negligence.

318
00:17:31,833 --> 00:17:32,867
I'm sorry, Vivian.

319
00:17:34,100 --> 00:17:35,300
Sorry?

320
00:17:35,367 --> 00:17:37,867
What can your sorry do?

321
00:17:37,933 --> 00:17:39,033
You failed me.

322
00:17:40,067 --> 00:17:42,500
I will talk again
to the investors.

323
00:17:42,567 --> 00:17:46,467
I promise that I'll ask them
to invest again in our business.

324
00:17:46,533 --> 00:17:49,800
Our business
is our top priority, Tonito.

325
00:17:49,900 --> 00:17:52,100
Our family worked hard for it.

326
00:17:53,267 --> 00:17:56,100
We are your family, not Celeste.

327
00:17:57,667 --> 00:18:00,867
Vivian, Celeste is my fiancé.

328
00:18:00,933 --> 00:18:02,567
She's my family now.

329
00:18:02,633 --> 00:18:04,267
Are we still going to argue
about this?

330
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:07,000
Yes, we are.

331
00:18:07,067 --> 00:18:09,700
We lost our investors
because of her.

332
00:18:10,733 --> 00:18:13,133
She is so unlike Aurelia.

333
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:16,300
Aurelia brings joy and pride
to the family.

334
00:18:16,367 --> 00:18:20,067
But that Celeste brings shame.

335
00:18:20,133 --> 00:18:21,500
Now, that is unfair!

336
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:26,000
You can't compare Aurelia
and Celeste.

337
00:18:26,067 --> 00:18:27,100
They are different people.

338
00:18:28,233 --> 00:18:31,867
And no matter what you say
about Celeste

339
00:18:31,933 --> 00:18:33,833
that won't stop me
from marrying her.

340
00:18:34,833 --> 00:18:38,033
And that won't stop me
from despising her.

341
00:19:23,633 --> 00:19:25,000
It might come out anytime.

342
00:19:25,067 --> 00:19:26,000
There's a hole.

343
00:19:26,067 --> 00:19:29,133
It might suddenly surprise us,
the bat.

344
00:19:29,233 --> 00:19:30,400
This is really it.

345
00:19:30,467 --> 00:19:32,000
Can it swim?

346
00:19:32,067 --> 00:19:35,533
Wait, Celeste, there's something
I will admit to you.

347
00:19:37,700 --> 00:19:39,700
Actually, there's no bat.

348
00:19:41,267 --> 00:19:43,133
I just made that up
when we were kids

349
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:46,133
so we can be close.

350
00:19:47,100 --> 00:19:49,333
And I brought you here
in Paguriran

351
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:50,467
to get rid of your fear

352
00:19:50,533 --> 00:19:53,300
and admit to you
that it's not true.

353
00:19:55,733 --> 00:19:56,367
What?

354
00:20:03,533 --> 00:20:05,500
Animal! You're annoying.

355
00:20:05,567 --> 00:20:08,567
Did you know
that I was traumatized

356
00:20:08,633 --> 00:20:10,300
thinking about it when I was
a child? I had nightmares.

357
00:20:10,367 --> 00:20:11,900
I carried that with me
until I got older.

358
00:20:13,033 --> 00:20:14,100
I'm sorry.

359
00:20:14,167 --> 00:20:16,267
That's the only way I thought of
when we were young

360
00:20:16,333 --> 00:20:18,400
to be closer to you.

361
00:20:18,467 --> 00:20:19,533
I'm naughty back then.

362
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:21,700
- You know that.
- Oh my God.

363
00:20:21,767 --> 00:20:23,767
Oh my God. You're annoying,

364
00:20:23,833 --> 00:20:25,700
- to be honest.
- Celeste...

365
00:20:25,767 --> 00:20:27,500
- Annoying!
- Celeste, I'm sorry.

366
00:20:27,567 --> 00:20:28,800
What do you mean I'm sorry?

367
00:20:28,867 --> 00:20:31,900
I had a fever
every time I think of that bat.

368
00:20:31,967 --> 00:20:33,100
And now, this?

369
00:20:33,167 --> 00:20:35,733
- Can you manage?
- I can manage!

370
00:20:35,833 --> 00:20:37,367
There's a bat!

371
00:20:37,433 --> 00:20:37,833
Where?

372
00:20:39,833 --> 00:20:41,333
Celeste, I'm sorry.

373
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:43,167
- Annoying!
- Take a video of her.

374
00:20:45,567 --> 00:20:46,733
Do you need help?

375
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:47,933
I don't.

376
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:48,700
Are you sure?

377
00:20:51,300 --> 00:20:52,133
I'm sure.

378
00:21:25,733 --> 00:21:26,800
Babe, chill.

379
00:21:29,100 --> 00:21:29,367
Hey...

380
00:21:38,700 --> 00:21:40,900
I'm sorry.
My jeep can't be fixed today.

381
00:21:40,967 --> 00:21:43,300
They need to buy
some spare parts in town.

382
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:45,967
Is there something else
that we can ride now?

383
00:21:46,033 --> 00:21:48,667
What I know is there are
no trips at this hour.

384
00:21:48,733 --> 00:21:50,567
But the trips will resume again
tomorrow.

385
00:21:50,633 --> 00:21:52,100
How can we go home?

386
00:21:52,167 --> 00:21:54,833
You can sleep at my house
tonight.

387
00:21:54,900 --> 00:21:56,233
Is there a hotel here?

388
00:21:56,300 --> 00:21:57,800
There's no hotel here.

389
00:21:57,867 --> 00:21:59,467
We are in a remote area.

390
00:22:00,567 --> 00:22:02,233
Where are we going to sleep?

391
00:22:02,300 --> 00:22:03,933
Here in my house.

392
00:22:07,100 --> 00:22:08,167
What?

393
00:22:08,233 --> 00:22:10,033
Just follow me inside.

394
00:22:10,100 --> 00:22:11,867
Sweetie pie, come on.

395
00:22:11,933 --> 00:22:12,967
Let's go to sleep.

396
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:15,700
Come on.

397
00:22:22,933 --> 00:22:24,667
Cuz, what happened?

398
00:22:24,733 --> 00:22:26,333
Are you still afraid?

399
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:28,667
I'm not afraid. I'm furious.

400
00:22:28,733 --> 00:22:29,967
Furious? What's furious?

401
00:22:30,033 --> 00:22:32,033
Irritated, angry, mad.

402
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:33,733
Angry? Why are you angry?

403
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:35,933
You should be happy because
you're not afraid anymore.

404
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:37,633
If he didn't scare me
and told me

405
00:22:37,700 --> 00:22:42,200
that there was a big bat there,
I wouldn't be traumatized.

406
00:22:42,267 --> 00:22:44,633
He took advantage
of my vulnerability

407
00:22:44,700 --> 00:22:46,567
with a vested interest.

408
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:49,733
- Give me my bag.
- My cousin speaks English

409
00:22:49,833 --> 00:22:50,733
- so fast.
- I'm sorry.

410
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:52,300
I'm hungry.

411
00:22:52,367 --> 00:22:53,833
I'll eat carbs.

412
00:22:53,900 --> 00:22:55,333
You're a fool, Mikoy.

413
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:57,233
Why did you do that?

414
00:22:57,300 --> 00:22:59,100
I'm still young then. Of course,
I was thinking

415
00:22:59,167 --> 00:23:00,100
a lot of nonsense.

416
00:23:00,167 --> 00:23:02,233
I want to make it up to her.

417
00:23:03,300 --> 00:23:04,833
It's annoying.

418
00:23:04,900 --> 00:23:06,133
I'm thrilled with you.

419
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:07,733
I hope it's for all.

420
00:23:10,367 --> 00:23:11,600
Cuz, wait!

421
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:40,567
Let's eat. I prepared this.

422
00:23:40,633 --> 00:23:41,000
Wow.

423
00:23:42,233 --> 00:23:45,000
Mikoy, come!

424
00:23:45,067 --> 00:23:46,933
Don't invite him.

425
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:49,800
Cuz, you should forgive Mikoy.

426
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:53,967
I'm sure he has done
a lot of good things.

427
00:23:54,033 --> 00:23:55,467
He only made a mistake once.

428
00:23:55,567 --> 00:23:57,333
You should forgive him.
What's with you?

429
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:59,667
I'm annoyed with him.

430
00:24:00,833 --> 00:24:02,133
Mikoy, come.

431
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:04,333
- Let's eat.
- No, don't invite him.

432
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:05,033
Come on.

433
00:24:11,733 --> 00:24:12,767
- That's a lot.
- It's delicious.

434
00:24:12,833 --> 00:24:14,600
Come here, Mikoy, hurry.

435
00:24:14,667 --> 00:24:15,700
There you go.

436
00:24:15,767 --> 00:24:16,100
Let's eat.

437
00:24:21,333 --> 00:24:22,633
This is your favorite, right?

438
00:24:22,700 --> 00:24:23,933
But you don't know
how to take the flesh out

439
00:24:26,067 --> 00:24:26,833
because of your fingernails.

440
00:24:35,733 --> 00:24:36,200
Do you want some more?

441
00:24:45,133 --> 00:24:49,733
Cuz, I noticed
you're the only one eating.

442
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:51,067
Let Mikoy eat too.

443
00:24:52,900 --> 00:24:53,600
Is that so?

444
00:24:57,367 --> 00:24:58,800
Let's roll this
so it's delicious.

445
00:25:03,500 --> 00:25:03,967
That's a lot.

446
00:25:07,300 --> 00:25:07,933
Thank you.

447
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:11,433
Sorry.

448
00:25:12,633 --> 00:25:13,100
Do you want fish?

449
00:25:17,100 --> 00:25:17,600
Some more fish?

450
00:25:37,533 --> 00:25:39,267
Babe, please don't act
like a child.

451
00:25:39,333 --> 00:25:40,633
We talked about this already.

452
00:25:40,700 --> 00:25:42,300
I know. But sleeping beside him?

453
00:25:42,367 --> 00:25:43,567
That's not part of the deal.

454
00:25:43,633 --> 00:25:45,067
It seems there's something
with Mikoy.

455
00:25:45,133 --> 00:25:46,200
What something?

456
00:25:46,267 --> 00:25:47,533
He still likes you.

457
00:25:47,600 --> 00:25:48,800
May I join you?

458
00:25:48,867 --> 00:25:50,967
Will you leave if I say no?

459
00:25:51,033 --> 00:25:52,033
Actually, no.

460
00:25:52,100 --> 00:25:53,333
I'm sorry.

461
00:25:53,400 --> 00:25:55,000
I shouldn't have done that.

462
00:25:55,067 --> 00:25:59,633
But maybe it's just part
of my frailties being a woman.

463
00:25:59,700 --> 00:26:01,600
Where is the shower here?

464
00:26:01,667 --> 00:26:03,733
It's over there.
I took a shower there.

465
00:26:03,800 --> 00:26:04,100
Okay.

466
00:26:06,667 --> 00:26:07,533
What are you doing?

467
00:26:07,600 --> 00:26:11,433
Oh my, I saw everything.

468
00:26:11,533 --> 00:26:12,567
As in everything?

469
00:26:12,633 --> 00:26:14,333
Side A, side B.

470
00:26:14,400 --> 00:26:17,133
Too bad, you should've tagged me
along so I can see it too.

471
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:18,433
There's no one there.

472
00:26:19,767 --> 00:26:23,600
Do you know where Mikoy
and Grandmother Ikay are?

473
00:26:23,667 --> 00:26:26,933
Let's pretend
we didn't part ways.

474
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:29,200
That it didn't happen

475
00:26:29,267 --> 00:26:31,467
and Tonito boy didn't come
into my life.

476
00:26:31,533 --> 00:26:35,200
We're still a couple
and I'm like this.

477
00:26:35,267 --> 00:26:36,267
Like this.

478
00:26:36,333 --> 00:26:38,267
Like me and all that jazz.

479
00:26:38,333 --> 00:26:39,800
Will you still love me?
